Summary
About the project
Soft Landing is a comprehensive web application designed for long-term travelers and digital nomads seeking their ideal living destination. The app simplifies the complex process of researching new cities by providing personalized cost-of-living reports based on individual lifestyle preferences. Users simply input "Which city are you curious to live in?" and receive detailed, customized reports that help them make informed decisions about their next adventure. The application goes beyond basic statistics by incorporating personal shopping habits and providing multimedia resources to give users a complete picture of life in their desired destination.

Tech Stack
Backend Framework: Flask (Python)
Database: SQLite
Web Scraping: BeautifulSoup4, Selenium WebDriver
Data Processing: Pandas DataFrames
Frontend Framework: Bootstrap 5
Programming Language: Python
Data Source: Numbeo.com
Video Integration: YouTube API
Additional Libraries: Requests, JSON handling
Main Goal
The primary objective of Soft Landing is to empower travelers with data-driven decision-making tools that facilitate destination selection based on:

Personalized Cost Analysis: Tailored to individual spending habits and lifestyle
Comparative City Analysis: Side-by-side comparison capabilities between multiple destinations
Historical Reference: Saved reports for future consultation and planning
Multimedia Insights: Curated video content to provide visual and cultural context
Lifestyle Integration: Custom cost calculations based on user's specific market shopping preferences
Functionalities
Core Features
1. City Research & Data Collection

Simple text input for city queries
Automated web scraping from Numbeo.com using BeautifulSoup and Selenium
Real-time data extraction including:
Housing costs and rental prices
Transportation expenses
Food and grocery prices
Entertainment and dining costs
Utilities and internet costs
Healthcare expenses
2. Personalized Market Calculator

Custom shopping list input feature
Users can specify items they plan to purchase regularly
Personalized cost estimation based on individual consumption patterns
Real-time price calculations for user's specific lifestyle needs
3. Data Management & Storage

Automatic DataFrame creation from scraped data
SQLite database integration for persistent storage
User history tracking and report archiving
Easy retrieval of previously researched cities
4. Cost of Living Analysis

Detailed breakdown by expense categories
Visual representations of cost distributions
Comparative analysis between different cities
Budget planning tools and recommendations
5. Multimedia Integration

Automated YouTube video curation with three specific queries per city:
"Where to go for eating in [City Name]"
"Quick Guide to [City Name]"
"Cost of Living in [City Name]"
Embedded video players within reports
Visual learning resources to complement statistical data
6. Report Generation & History

Comprehensive city reports with all collected data
Personal shopping cost estimates
Historical report access for comparison
Export and sharing capabilities
Bootstrap Design
Design Architecture
The application leverages Bootstrap 5's powerful framework to deliver a responsive, mobile-first design that ensures optimal user experience across all devices and screen sizes.

Key Design Components
Navigation & Layout

Responsive Navbar: Fixed-top navigation with brand logo and menu items
Fluid Container System: Bootstrap's grid system for consistent spacing
Mobile-First Approach: Seamless experience on smartphones, tablets, and desktops
User Interface Elements

Search Interface: Prominent search bar with Bootstrap input groups and validation
Progress Indicators: Loading spinners and progress bars during data scraping operations
Alert System: Success, warning, and error messages using Bootstrap alert components
Modal Dialogs: For settings, confirmations, and detailed information display
Content Organization

Card Layout: Bootstrap cards for organizing different report sections
Tabbed Interface: Navigation tabs for switching between cost categories
Accordion Components: Collapsible sections for detailed breakdowns
List Groups: Organized display of market items and costs
Data Presentation

Tables: Responsive Bootstrap tables for cost comparisons
Badge Components: Highlighting important metrics and categories
Progress Bars: Visual representation of cost percentages and comparisons
Visual Design Elements

Color Scheme: Professional light-gray, gray, white, black and  palette representing trust and growth
Typography: Bootstrap's typography scale for